notes.note:
Sean, 
I sent the email to you the day before I left for holidays and followed up today after speaking with Craig. Craig was originally taking care of this claim. I took over as he was sick. Regardless, I do apologize for not calling you. 
Bases on our conversation mainly being by email, I thought this would be the best way of communicating with you.  
I do understand your frustration. 
However, I do have guidelines to follow for all warranty claims when it comes to engine repairs there is no wiggle room when it comes to maintenance. 
I was trying to sort the situation as quickly as possible for you. 
When authorizing the claim we always ask for maintenance, for some reason I thought this step was already taken.
When looking for your maintenance, a good online tool is CARFAX.  Hopefully this speeds the process up. The free CARFAX will give you the dealers that changed the oil then you just need to call and ask them fora copy of the invoice.   
Kindest Regards, 
Sean Terkildsen
